Seton Keough's Yasmin Lewis talks about 42 37 win over Catonsville. (Craig Clary/BSMG) Katherine Dunn in Pennsylvania.
The "ELITE 100" includes 127 players. Team Maryland and Arundel coach Chuck Markiewicz said the number discrepency is because some coaches missed the deadline for nominations, but Team Maryland officials did not want to leave any of the top players out because of the delay. 
The players will be invited to tryout combines on Feb. 12 and Feb. 26. The first combine will be held at the Baltimore Ravens Under Armour Performance Center; the second will be held at another location because of construction at the Ravens' Owings Mills complex. 
After the tryouts, Markiewicz and his staff -- including River Hill coach Brian Van Deusen, who heads the selection committe -- will choose 34 players for Team Maryland. 
The list of nominees includes players from 22 local schools -- 10 from the MIAA and 12 from public schools. Both of The Baltimore Sun's players of the year -- Archbishop Spalding quarterback Evan Fochtman and St. Frances linebacker Sam Thomas -- are among the 26 MIAA players who made the cut.
